    "body": "If there is whitespace or brackets, `()`, in the path, problems occur.\r\nI'm using the [first movie example](https://docs.generic-mapping-tools.org/dev/movie.html#examples) *globe.sh* to create the error.\r\n\r\nWhitespace:\r\n```\r\n$ pwd\r\n/home/anbj/anbj-220509T103758/hello there\r\n\r\n$ gmt movie globe.sh -Nglobe -T2 -Fgif -C6ix6ix100 -Lf -P -Z\r\nmovie [NOTICE]: Running: gm convert -delay 4 -loop 1 +dither /home/anbj/anbj-220509T103758/hello there/globe/globe_*.png globe.gif\r\ngm convert: Unable to open file (/home/anbj/anbj-220509T103758/hello) [No such file or directory].\r\nmovie [ERROR]: Running GIF conversion returned error 256 - exiting.\r\n```\r\n\r\nBracket(s):\r\n```\r\n$ pwd\r\n/home/anbj/anbj-220509T103758/hello(there)\r\n\r\n$ gmt movie globe.sh -Nglobe -T2 -Fgif -C6ix6ix100 -Lf -P -Z\r\nmovie [NOTICE]: Running: gm convert -delay 4 -loop 1 +dither /home/anbj/anbj-220509T103758/hello(there)/globe/globe_*.png globe.gif\r\nsh: 1: Syntax error: \"(\" unexpected\r\nmovie [ERROR]: Running GIF conversion returned error 512 - exiting.\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you instead of a gif, want an mp4, the error is slightly different, but same cause I think:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ pwd\r\n/home/anbj/anbj-220509T103758/hello(there)\r\n\r\n$ gmt movie globe.sh -Nglobe -T2 -Fmp4 -C6ix6ix100 -Lf -P -Z\r\nmovie [NOTICE]: Running: ffmpeg -loglevel warning -f image2 -framerate 24 -y -i \"/home/anbj/anbj-220509T103758/hello(there)/globe/globe_%01d.png\" -vcodec libx264  -pix_fmt yuv420p globe.mp4\r\nmovie_cleanup.sh: line 3: syntax error near unexpected token `('\r\nmovie_cleanup.sh: line 3: `rm -rf /home/anbj/anbj-220509T103758/hello(there)/globe'\r\nmovie [ERROR]: Running cleanup script movie_cleanup.sh returned error 512 - exiting.\r\n```\r\n\r\nBonus:\r\nAlthough it doesn't really makes sense, if you set `-T1`, you get into trouble:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ gmt movie globe.sh -Nglobe -T1 -Fgif -C6ix6ix100 -Lf -P -Z\r\nError: /undefined in -nan\r\nOperand stack:\r\n   180\r\nExecution stack:\r\n   %interp_exit   .runexec2   --nostringval--   --nostringval--   --nostringval--   2   %stopped_push   --nostringval--   --nostringval--   --nostringval--   false   1   %stopped_push   1990   1   3   %oparray_pop   1989   1   3   %oparray_pop   1977   1   3   %oparray_pop   1833   1   3   %oparray_pop   --nostringval--   %errorexec_pop   .runexec2   --nostringval--   --nostringval--   --nostringval--   2   %stopped_push   --nostringval--   --nostringval--\r\nDictionary stack:\r\n   --dict:744/1123(ro)(G)--   --dict:0/20(G)--   --dict:75/200(L)--   --dict:159/250(L)--\r\nCurrent allocation mode is local\r\nCurrent file position is 441802\r\nGPL Ghostscript 9.53.3: Unrecoverable error, exit code 1\r\npsconvert [ERROR]: System call [gs -q -dNOPAUSE -dBATCH -dNOSAFER -dSCANCONVERTERTYPE=2 -dMaxBitmap=2147483647 -dUseFastColor=true -dGraphicsAlphaBits=2 -dTextAlphaBits=4 -sDEVICE=png16m  -g600x600 -r100 -sOutputFile='../globe_0.png' '/home/anbj/.gmt/sessions/gmt_session.92643/psconvert_92649d.eps'] returned error 256.\r\nend [ERROR]: Failed to call psconvert\r\nend [ERROR]: gmtinit_process_figures returned error 79\r\n```",
